textBeforeTable: Here is the pinout of the 20-pin power connector: OK, there's a little more to it than that.  The 20-pin connector is the older [tag]ATX[/tag] 1.x standard while the 24-pin connector belongs to the newer ATX 2.x standard.  One has a 20-pin [tag]motherboard[/tag] connector, the other has a 24-pin connector!  What's the difference between a [tag]20-pin[/tag] [tag]PSU[/tag] and a [tag]24-pin[/tag] power supply unit (PSU)? google_color_text = "666666"; google_color_url = "666666"; google_color_link = "0066CC"; google_color_bg = "FFFFFF"; google_color_border = "FFFFFF"; google_ad_channel =""; google_ad_type = "text"; google_ad_format = "120x240_as"; google_ad_height = 240; google_ad_width = 120; google_ad_client = "pub-0991230877927971"; //--> google_ad_height = 15; google_ad_width
